explanation: The solution uses a difference array to count character frequencies in the two halves of the string. It then checks for each query whether the characters in the specified ranges can be rearranged to make the string a palindrome. The key insight is that the counts of characters in the two ranges must be equal for the string to be a palindrome. The solution also checks whether the ranges overlap sufficiently to allow for the required rearrangement.
